Hungary May Increase Tax on Drugmakers, Napi Gazdasag Reports

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-04-11T06:21:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/hungary-may-increase-tax-on-drugmakers-napi-gazdasag-reports.html
Hungary may raise a special tax on
pharmaceutical companies to 18 percent from 12 percent,  Napi
Gazdasag  reported, citing a document it obtained.  The tax may be increased to as much as 50 percent on sales
of subsidized drugs to help reduce health-care expenditures, the
newspaper said.  The government also plans to double a tax on drug company
sales representatives who visit doctors to 10 million forint
($55,000) a year from 5 million forint as of July 1, Napi
Gazdasag said.  The cabinet may also consider regulating drug prices, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz in Budapest at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  